<p>We evolve it in time (i.e. encode its interactions) by multiplying the state by â€˜time-evolution gatesâ€™. For a local, periodic Hamiltonian, the result for the new state after time $t$ looks like this<sup id="fnref:4" role="doc-noteref"><a href="#fn:4" class="footnote" rel="footnote">4</a></sup>,</p>

